<subSubSection id="34B965357C47FF8C5D96FB2BFD088976" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7C1C36BE7C47FF8C5D96FB2BFD088976" blockId="13.[151,1436,1051,1544]" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">
Comment. The justification of the generic assignement of 
<taxonomicName id="BBA34D3D7C47FF8C5E29FB34FC0C8B96" authority="Kirkaldy, 1905" authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1905" box="[808,963,1232,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psyllia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beeryi">
<emphasis id="4ED7EAAC7C47FF8C5E29FB34FC0C8B96" box="[808,963,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">Psyllia beeryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="18324B4F7C47FF8C5EEFFB2BFB698B99" author="Caldwell, J. S." box="[1006,1190,1231,1255]" firstAuthor="Caldwell" journalOrPublisher="Journal Of The New York Entomological Society" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" pagination="335 - 341" part="52" refId="ref10560" refString="Caldwell, J. S. (1944) Psylliidae from tropical and semitropical America (Homoptera). Journal Of The New York Entomological Society, 52, 335 - 341." title="Psylliidae from tropical and semitropical America (Homoptera)" type="journal article" year="1944">
Caldwell (
<number id="CA6B24997C47FF8C5962FB2BFB518B99" box="[1123,1182,1231,1255]" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" value="1944.0">1944</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
was relatively vague. He stated: ‘The gigantic development of the genae sets this species apart from any psyllid known to me; however, the structure of the entire insect is true to the genus.’ 
<bibRefCitation id="18324B4F7C47FF8C5EA2FAFCFB298A51" author="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D." box="[931,1254,1303,1327]" editor="L. Lyneborg" firstAuthor="Brown" journalOrPublisher="Leiden, New York, Kopenhagen, Koln" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" pagination="304" refId="ref9423" refString="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D. (1988) Taxonomy and ecology of the jumping plant-lice of Panama (Homoptera: Psylloidea). In: L. Lyneborg (Ed), Entomonograph. E. J. Brill, Scandinavian Science Press Ltd., Leiden, New York, Kopenhagen, Koln, p. 304." title="Taxonomy and ecology of the jumping plant-lice of Panama (Homoptera: Psylloidea)" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Entomonograph. E. J. Brill, Scandinavian Science Press Ltd" year="1988">
Brown &amp; Hodkinson (
<number id="CA6B24997C47FF8C59A5FAF3FB118A51" box="[1188,1246,1303,1327]" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" value="1988.0">1988</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the species and transferred it without comment to 
<taxonomicName id="BBA34D3D7C47FF8C5FD6FAD8FCAE8A2A" box="[727,865,1340,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Limbopsylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4ED7EAAC7C47FF8C5FD6FAD8FCAE8A2A" box="[727,865,1340,1364]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">Limbopsylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which, according to them, contains species of the subfamilies Acizziinae and Ciriacreminae with unclear phylogenetic relationships. Larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="BBA34D3D7C47FF8C59D8FA85FA8B8A06" authority="Kirkaldy, 1905" authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1905" box="[1241,1348,1376,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psyllia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beeryi">
<emphasis id="4ED7EAAC7C47FF8C59D8FA85FA8B8A06" box="[1241,1348,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">M. beeryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="1AB2AE7B7C47FF8C5853FABBFA588A09" box="[1362,1431,1375,1399]" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">ELEF</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="1AB2AE7B7C47FF8C5DC6FA60FED28AE2" box="[199,285,1412,1436]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/1d5a-4efs" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Basel" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">NHMB</collectionCode>
) bear pore fields in addition to the circumanal ring, a defining feature of Macrocorsinae. The presence of thick, downwards directed genal processes which are apically subacute or blunt but not incised, suggest a relationship to the Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName id="BBA34D3D7C47FF8C5F26FA29FC8A8A9A" authority="Vo" authorityName="Vo" box="[551,837,1485,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Macrocorsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congensis">
<emphasis id="4ED7EAAC7C47FF8C5F26FA29FCEC8A9A" box="[551,803,1485,1508]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">Macrocorsa congensis</emphasis>
Vo
</taxonomicName>
n d r á ček. Here we transfer 
<taxonomicName id="BBA34D3D7C47FF8C596EFA28FAC68A9A" authority="Kirkaldy, 1905" authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1905" box="[1135,1289,1484,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psyllia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beeryi">
<emphasis id="4ED7EAAC7C47FF8C596EFA28FAC68A9A" box="[1135,1289,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">Psyllia beeryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to this genus as 
<taxonomicName id="BBA34D3D7C47FF8C5DE4FA15FDF38979" authority="Caldwell" authorityName="Caldwell" box="[229,572,1519,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Macrocorsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beeryi" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="4ED7EAAC7C47FF8C5DE4FA15FE758976" box="[229,442,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">Macrocorsa beeryi</emphasis>
(Caldwell)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="55E457D77C47FF8C5F47FA14FD088976" box="[582,711,1520,1544]" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="4ED7EAAC7C47FF8C5F47FA14FD088976" bold="true" box="[582,711,1520,1544]" pageId="13" pageNumber="39">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
